FBIS4-65849 "drweu100_q_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-100 Daily Report 20 May 1994 TURKEY Security Forces Continue Operations Against PKK Security Forces Continue Operations Against PKK 15 `Terrorists' Die in Agri TA2005103894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 GMT 20 May 94 TA2005103894 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] Fifteen terrorists belonging to the PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] terrorist organization have been killed in clashes with the security forces in Agri's Tendurek Mountains. According to information obtained by a Turkish Radio and Television correspondent, many weapons and large amounts of ammunition have been seized in the area. The operation continues. Four persons were killed when a private car hit a mine laid by terrorists near the Topluca village of Mardin's Savur District.
